<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}+{7}{y}={47}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}-{2}{y}={30}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{8},{9}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}+{7}{y}={47}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}={47}-{\left({7}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{47}-{\left({7}{y}\right)}}}{{2}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{\left(\frac{{{47}-{\left({7}{y}\right)}}}{{2}}\right)}+-{2}{y}={30}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{6}}{{2}}\cdot{\left({47}\right)}--\frac{{6}}{{2}}{\left({7}\right)}{y}+-{2}{y}={30}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{141}-{\left({21}\right)}{y}+-{2}{y}={30}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{21}{y}+{\left(-{2}\right)}{y}={30}--{141}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{21}{y}+{\left(-{2}\right)}{y}={171}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({21}+{\left(-{2}\right)}\right)}{y}={171}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{19}{y}={171}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{171}}{{19}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={9}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}+{7}{\left({9}\right)}={47}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}+{\left({63}\right)}={47}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}={47}-{\left({63}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}=-{16}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{16}}{{2}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{8}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{8},{9}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

